article.headline: Temple 57, Fordham 47
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- David Hawkins scored 28 points, setting a school record with his 13th consecutive game with more than 20, and Temple beat Fordham 57-47 Wednesday night, the Owls' 18th straight win over the Rams. Hawkins scored 22 points in the second half when the Owls (8-10, 3-5 Atlantic 10) rallied from an eight-point deficit by holding Fordham to seven points in the final 11 minutes. Michael Haynes had 19 points and eight rebounds for the Rams (4-14, 1-6), who lost their fifth straight overall and saw their losing streak in February extend to 18 games, a run that dates to 2001. Mark Jarrell-Wright's free throw with 11:18 to play gave Fordham a 40-32 lead. The Owls scored the game's next 12 points, the last seven by Hawkins, to start an 18-1 run that gave them a 50-41 lead with 3:58 to play. Fordham was 7-for-24 from the field in the second half (29.2 percent), including missing seven shots during its 8:46 drought without a field goal during the Owls' run. Hawkins had six points on 2-for-11 shooting in the opening 20 minutes as the Owls fell behind 24-21 with their lowest first-half point total of the season. The senior guard entered the game fourth in nation in scoring with an average of 23.9 points and leading Division I in percentage of his team's points scored at 38 percent. Hawkins finished 9-for-22 from the field, including 3-for-12 from 3-point range, and 7-for-8 from the free-throw line. He had eight rebounds as the Owls finished with a 47-24 advantage on the boards. Hawkins had been tied for the school record of 12 straight games over 20 points with Bill Mlkvy, who did it in 1950-51. Fordham last beat Temple on Dec. 5, 1981.
